<a href="apigee.com/docs/enterprise/enterprise_home">Home</a> > <a href="/api-resources">Platform API Reference</a> > <a href="/api_resources/37-users">Users</a> > Associate a user with a user role</div>

<h1>Associate a user with a user role</h1> 
</p>

<div class="row">
	<div class="span6" style="width:340px;"><p>
		<b>API Platform Base Path:</b>
		<h3><p>https://api.enterprise.apigee.com/v1/o/{org_name}</p></h3>
		<b>API Resource Path:</b>
		<p>/users/{user_email}/userroles</p>
		<p>
		Associates a user with one or more roles
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="span6" style="width:340px;">
		<p>
		<b>Verb:</b>
		<span class="verb-POST">POST</span>
		</p>
		<b>Auth:</b>
		Basic Auth
		</p>


	</div>
</div>

<div class="span18">
	<p>
	Note : The API call will return an error if one of the roles is invalid or does not exist. The role must belong to the organization scope.
	</p>

	<b>cURL:</b>
	<pre>curl -u myname:mypass https://api.enterprise.apigee.com/v1/o/{myorg}/users/{userEmail}/userroles</pre>



<b>Sample Response:</b> 
	<pre>Success 2xx with proper response
{
  "role" : [ {
    "name" : "apiproxyadmin"
  }, {
    "name" : "reportsadmin"
  } ]
}</pre>




</div>


            </div>
        </div><!--/row-->
      </div><!--/content-->

